Feature: Remote Agent Commands Registration and Reactive Querying in ACP

  Background:
    Given Codeprompt ACP server is running
    And a remote agent "ExternalAssistant" is available via ACP
    And the graph state contains initial context

  @scenario1 @registration
  Scenario: Sc1 - List of remote agent commands should be registrable in ACP
    Given a RemoteCommandRegistry is available
    And the following remote commands are defined:
      | command_name    | description                    | parameters         | return_type |
      | analyze-code    | Analyze source code            | code, language     | analysis    |
      | generate-docs   | Generate documentation         | code, style        | string      |
      | validate-syntax | Validate code syntax           | code, language     | boolean     |
      | run-tests       | Execute unit tests             | test_path          | test_result |

    When I register all remote commands with ACP
    Then the commands are successfully registered
    And ACP server contains all 4 commands in the registry
    And each command has the correct metadata (name, description, parameters)

    When the CodingPrompt agent retrieves its info via getAgentInfo()
    Then the response includes the complete list of registered remote commands
    And external agents can discover these commands through ACP

  @scenario1 @registration @execution
  Scenario: Remote command can be executed through graph node
    Given the remote command "analyze-code" is registered in ACP
    And the CodingPromptGraph includes a RemoteCommandExecutorNode
    And the LLM generates a tool call for "analyze-code"

    When the graph processes the LLM response
    Then the RemoteCommandExecutorNode intercepts the command request
    And the command is looked up in the RemoteCommandRegistry
    And the command is executed with the provided parameters
    And the result is merged back into the graph state
    And the graph continues execution with the command result

  @scenario1 @registration @validation
  Scenario: Invalid remote commands are rejected
    Given the RemoteCommandRegistry is available
    And I attempt to register a command with missing parameters

    When I try to register an incomplete command
    Then the registration fails with a validation error
    And the invalid command is not added to the registry
    And ACP is not notified of the failed registration

  @scenario2 @reactive-query
  Scenario: Sc2 - A node should be able to reactively query another agent
    Given the graph execution is at the "agent" node
    And the LLM response contains "[QUERY_EXTERNAL]" directive
    And "ExternalAssistant" agent is available via ACP
    And ReactiveAgentQueryNode is part of the graph

    When the graph routes to ReactiveAgentQueryNode
    Then the node builds an AgentQueryRequest from current state
    And the request is sent to ExternalAssistant via ACP
    And the graph does not block waiting for the response

    When ExternalAssistant processes the query
    Then the response is received by ReactiveAgentQueryNode
    And the response is converted to ChatMessage format
    And the message is appended to the graph state
    And the graph resumes execution with the new context
